\fs42 \cf5 \strokec5 This strategy has helped Costco retain members through the U.S. economic recession, though the company did see a string of monthly declines in sales at established stores from October 2008 through August 2009, after financial markets tumbled following Lehman Brothers\'92 collapse.\
Other retailers also felt pressure as shoppers held back, and many continue to underperform Costco. Wal-Mart Stores Inc\'a0WMT.N\'a0has posted nine straight quarters of sales declines at established stores, though sales have been growing at its Sam's Club warehouse chain.\
Shares of Costco have risen nearly 40 percent in the past year, whereas Wal-Mart shares are up just 6 percent even though the world's largest retailer enjoys a gross profit margin of close to 25 percent compared with Costco's 10.8 percent. Shares of another competitor, BJ's Wholesale Club Inc\'a0BJ.N, have risen about 21 percent over the last year.\
