\f0\fs44 \cf5 LONG-TIME LIEUTENANT\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1120\fi-1120\sa600\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs42 \cf5 Sinegal plans to step down as CEO on January 1, 2012, his 76th birthday, though he will remain with the retailer for another year to help with the transition.\
Those who follow Costco do not expect big changes under Jelinek, who got his start at the company as a warehouse manager in 1984 and was long seen as the next CEO once Sinegal decided to retire.\
Jelinek has been Costco\'92s president and chief operating officer since February 2010.\
\'93We do not think the strategic vision of the company will change,\'94 said Credit Suisse analyst Michael Exstein. \'93Craig Jelinek has been the heir apparent for some time and we believe he is well equipped to continue executing the company\'92s vision in his new role.\'94\
In an interview with the Seattle Times, Sinegal said his age and the fact that Costco is in good shape made January the right time to step down as CEO.
