\fs42 \cf5 \strokec5 Members often recognize Sinegal when he visits stores, though he does not have quite the cult following of another West Coast CEO who recently announced he was stepping down.\
\'93He is the most prominent CEO in terms of setting corporate culture that I can recall,\'94 said Trutina\'92s Edwards, whose firm holds some Costco shares, though not as many as in the past because the stock price has gone up.\
\'93He\'92s basically the retail Steve Jobs,\'94 she said.\
However, Costco shoppers have to go elsewhere for any of Apple Inc's\'a0AAPL.O\'a0iPads, iPhones or other gadgets. Sam's Club is the exclusive warehouse chain for Apple products.\
Like Jobs, who famously earned $1 a year, Sinegal has kept his own salary constant for years and relied on stock holdings in the company to increase his net worth.\
Sinegal has earned $350,000 a year since fiscal 1999, and Costco\'92s board has often commented on how the company\'92s executives are underpaid.\
It remains to be seen if that changes under Jelinek, though he isn\'92t answering his own phone.\
A call to Jelinek\'92s office on Thursday was answered by a live person. Not Jelinek himself. Not even his recording.\
